{"TopicId":179587,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"A \u0026quot;KSP Loading...\u0026quot; Preview: Activate Navigation to Launchsite","CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T18:50:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T18:50:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022360\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://gfycat.com/ifr/BrilliantParallelCow\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://gfycat.com/BrilliantParallelCow\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Evia Gfycat\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EWe are including a new quality of life feature in update 1.6 to help pilots find their way back to a Launchsite or Runway!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EPlayers will now be able to activate the navigation system towards the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E, the Woomerang Launch Site, the Island Runway, \u00A0Dessert Launch Site or any mobile Launchsite set by a mission creator. Activate Navigation to a Launchsite will target the chosen location and add a navigation mark in the NavBall. Players will be able to activate this feature from the Map View at any time.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbalstar","CreatedById":154159,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:02:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, and looking good \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E! Also, first!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XLjedi","CreatedById":175658,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:07:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...that\u0027s not too far off from just adding a waypoint manager, is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lupi","CreatedById":86088,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\noooh! this is a nice little thing! makes those launch site icons super useful!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaverickSawyer","CreatedById":11952,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:21:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice! And second time\u0027s the charm. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:27:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill this be for Making History only or in stock?\u00A0 And will it be accessible for modders (looking at you kerbal konstructs!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T19:54:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541532443\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122369\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022theJesuit\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, theJesuit said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill this be for Making History only or in stock?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably stock, as we got the launch site icons in stock KSP 1.4.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd this is pretty cool, by the way! It will certainly make it easier to find our way back to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E (and the other sites too).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Poodmund","CreatedById":128643,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T20:04:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice to see this bug get fixed (the bug being that we were unable to do so previously). \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0Introducing a UI to allow us to set and store waypoints and enable them would also be brilliant... oh wait... errr... something something Waypoint Manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Just realised that we will also no longer have to plant flags at the start of the runways.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-06T20:05:53Z\u0022 title=\u002211/06/2018 08:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 6, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Poodmund\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T21:48:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA surprise to be sure, but a welcome one!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T21:59:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving planted flags at the runways and parked automated probes at the runway ends as well in years past, I have to say that this new feature is a welcome change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T22:22:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541534094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will certainly make it easier to find our way back to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting to do it by rightclicking a site icon is a nice addition of course, but we\u0027ve been able to place arbitrary navigation waypoints in stock since before 1.4, through the console and with KerbNet. (console: /\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003Eksc\u003C/abbr\u003E and /waypoint \u0026lt;body\u0026gt; \u0026lt;lat\u0026gt; \u0026lt;long\u0026gt; \u0026lt;name\u0026gt;).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541534694\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128643\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Poodmund\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Poodmund said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust realised that we will also no longer have to plant flags at the start of the runways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still prefer using two flags beyond the ends of the runways instead of waypoints - the target brackets make for better approach alignment indicators than the waypoint icons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GrandProtectorDark","CreatedById":183946,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T23:14:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool thing. Am Only hoping like everyone else, for a waypoint manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch site beacon signal is still something really useful. Good job\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T23:43:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541546045\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183946\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GrandProtectorDark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, GrandProtectorDark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool thing. Am Only hoping like everyone else, for a waypoint manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch site beacon signal is still something really useful. Good job\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you mean this? KerbNet\u0027s waypoint markers are something like this. (Personally, I like the mod much more.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5652758709\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/94432-15x-waypoint-manager-v274-2018-10-21/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GrandProtectorDark","CreatedById":183946,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-06T23:50:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI completely forgot about kerbnet.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSquad do could try to expand kerbnet with a few more functions to make it useful.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T00:09:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHarrumph. In my day we didn\u0027t know where we were and we couldn\u0027t find things, and we \u003Cu\u003Eliked \u003C/u\u003Eit that way.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaverickSawyer","CreatedById":11952,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T00:23:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482578\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541549390\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHarrumph. In my day we didn\u0027t know where we were and we couldn\u0027t find things, and we \u003Cu\u003Eliked \u003C/u\u003Eit that way.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lol.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002215\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.orbiter-forum.com/images/smilies/lol.gif\u0022 width=\u002215\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T00:24:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541532443\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122369\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022theJesuit\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, theJesuit said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill this be for Making History only or in stock?\u00A0 And will it be accessible for modders (looking at you kerbal konstructs!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s stock - but accounts for all launchsites stock, or stock available with Making History and including Making History - Mission mobile launchsites.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYes it will be accessible to modders - with a bit of code you could write some mod code to add markers for just about anything anywhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chakat Firepaw","CreatedById":150121,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T03:25:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541534694\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128643\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Poodmund\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Poodmund said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Just realised that we will also no longer have to plant flags at the start of the runways.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou still might want to, so that you have a pair of markers for alignment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T03:31:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482589\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541550263\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s stock - but accounts for all launchsites stock, or stock available with Making History and including Making History - Mission mobile launchsites.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYes it will be accessible to modders - with a bit of code you could write some mod code to add markers for just about anything anywhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis really looks like a great feature!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou say \u201Ccode\u201D but is there a chance that \u00A0new locations could be added via .cfg file?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would really open this interesting feature up for us sub-coders and\u00A0config wranglers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T05:48:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541561484\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis really looks like a great feature!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou say \u201Ccode\u201D but is there a chance that \u00A0new locations could be added via .cfg file?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would really open this interesting feature up for us sub-coders and\u00A0config wranglers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. code would be required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-20T19:38:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541569689\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/6/2018 at 9:48 PM, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. code would be required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the response.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwill there be any new launchsites coming in 1.6?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ruedii","CreatedById":57704,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T00:12:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be nice if there was a number indicating heading.\u00A0 When within a certain distance it should give glideslope to target as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cassel","CreatedById":181728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T10:01:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was playing with asymmetrical rockets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022a4aIl5U.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/a4aIl5U.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand they are great if you have Mechjeb to use thrust vectoring during flight, but when I would want to fly it manually it is boring... so maybe we could have new feature on Navball? If you click at any point on Navball \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is trying to hold find shortest path to that direction and hold it using thrust vectoring, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T14:02:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542794481\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181728\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cassel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Cassel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand they are great if you have Mechjeb to use thrust vectoring during flight, but when I would want to fly it manually it is boring... so maybe we could have new feature on Navball? If you click at any point on Navball \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is trying to hold find shortest path to that direction and hold it using thrust vectoring, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/97154-145-throttle-controlled-avionics/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EThrottle Contolled Avionics\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ozymandias_the_Goat","CreatedById":159377,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T16:17:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdmittedly I would do a very simmilar\u00A0thing to line up with a runway, as I would put a target probe right in front of the runway, and set it as a target, although I usually don\u2019t need them anymore. Nice that there is a feature to do this anyhow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, it\u2019s not completely true\u00A0that I never use target probaes,\u00A0as they allow one to smash into various Easter eggs at orbital speed with great ease.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}